# ProjectUltra – Cursor Project Rules

## 1. Architecture & Data

- Use **mock data layer** only for sample data in `src/api/mockData.js`
- When adding features: `mockData` → API wrapper (`src/api/*.js`) → Pinia store (`src/stores/*.js`) → components

## 2. Components & Reuse

- Always **reuse shared widgets**, never fork duplicates
- Check for existing components before creating new ones

## 3. Styling & Layout

- **Responsive**: Tables remove columns (no horizontal scroll); filters above content; buttons aligned right
- **Tailwind**: 
  - NO arbitrary values (`w-[350px]`, `text-[14px]`) - use semantic classes only
  - Use semantic tokens: `text-primary`, `bg-surface`, `border-border` (from `tailwind.config.js`)
  - Mobile-first: `class="flex flex-col md:flex-row"` (not `max-md:`)
  - Use Flexbox/Grid for layout, avoid floats/hardcoded heights

## 4. Build & Deploy

- Run `npm run build` before pushing
- Never commit `dist/`
- Netlify builds from source via `netlify.toml`

## 5. Clean Code

- Remove unused components immediately
- No `console.log` in stores/widgets/shared components (debug only, then delete)
- Delete old files + imports + routes when refactoring
- No commented-out code

## 6. Component Style (Vue 3)

- Use `<script setup>` for all components
- Naming: Components `PascalCase.vue`, composables `useSomething.js`, stores `useXStore`
- Prefer alias imports: `@/components/...`, `@/stores/...`
- All shared state through Pinia stores only

## 7. Refactoring

- Files >200 lines with mixed responsibilities → extract subcomponents or composables
- Prefer composition over adding to large files

## 8. Modals & Placeholders

- **Always wrap modals** with `ModalShell.vue` from `@/components/shared/ModalShell.vue`
- **Unimplemented features**: Open `ComingSoonModal` from `@/components/shared/ComingSoonModal.vue`

Example:
```vue
<template>
  <ModalShell :show="show" @close="$emit('close')" title="Title">
    <!-- content -->
  </ModalShell>
  <!-- For unimplemented: -->
  <ComingSoonModal :show="showComingSoon" @close="showComingSoon = false" />
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue'
import ModalShell from '@/components/shared/ModalShell.vue'
import ComingSoonModal from '@/components/shared/ComingSoonModal.vue'

const showComingSoon = ref(false)
</script>
```
